{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013mFJjFJYjubR2aPh9CEyiZ","type":"tool_result","content":"Active code page: 65001\r\ncommit cb787cc0c7edd91d245175af439a9190da97228b\nAuthor: Victor M. Alvarez <vmalvarez@virustotal.com>\nDate:   Wed Jul 25 13:26:52 2018 +0200\n\n    Fix issue #920.\n\ndiff --git a/libyara/parser.c b/libyara/parser.c\nindex 6789a341..dd696f6d 100644\n--- a/libyara/parser.c\n+++ b/libyara/parser.c\n@@ -730,7 +730,7 @@ int yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1(\n       yr_hash_table_lookup(\n         compiler->objects_table,\n         identifier,\n-        compiler->current_namespace->name) != NULL)\n+        NULL) != NULL)\n   {\n     // A rule or variable with the same identifier already exists, return the\n     // appropriate error.\ndiff --git a/tests/test-api.c b/tests/test-api.c\nindex b2c5ef8d..c0877e7c 100644\n--- a/tests/test-api.c\n+++ b/tests/test-api.c\n@@ -694,6 +694,42 @@ void test_rules_stats()\n }\n \n \n+void test_issue_920()\n+{\n+  const char* rules_str = \"\\\n+      rule test { \\\n+        condition: true \\\n+      }\";\n+\n+  YR_COMPILER* compiler = NULL;\n+\n+  yr_initialize();\n+\n+  if (yr_compiler_create(&compiler) != ERROR_SUCCESS)\n+  {\n+    perror(\"yr_compiler_create\");\n+    exit(EXIT_FAILURE);\n+  }\n+\n+  // Define a variable named \"test\"\n+  yr_compiler_define_boolean_variable(compiler, \"test\", 1);\n+\n+  // The compilation should not succeed, as the rule is named \"test\" and a\n+  // a variable with the same name already exists.\n+  yr_compiler_add_string(compiler, rules_str, NULL);\n+\n+  if (compiler->last_error != ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER)\n+  {\n+    yr_compiler_destroy(compiler);\n+    printf(\"expecting ERROR_CALLBACK_REQUIRED (%d), got: %d\\n\",\n+           ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER, compiler->last_error);\n+    exit(EXIT_FAILURE);\n+  }\n+\n+  yr_compiler_destroy(compiler);\n+  yr_finalize();\n+}\n+\n int main(int argc, char** argv)\n {\n   test_disabled_rules();\n@@ -704,6 +740,8 @@ int main(int argc, char** argv)\n   test_save_load_rules();\n   test_scanner();\n   test_ast_callback();\n-  test_issue_834();\n   test_rules_stats();\n+\n+  test_issue_834();\n+  test_issue_920();\n }","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3add790f-caa9-4081-a140-ecdff77df695","uuid":"6731f442-b5fa-45ed-a192-0a9039f472ab","timestamp":"2026-05-04T02:22:50.400Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Active code page: 65001\r\ncommit cb787cc0c7edd91d245175af439a9190da97228b\nAuthor: Victor M. Alvarez <vmalvarez@virustotal.com>\nDate:   Wed Jul 25 13:26:52 2018 +0200\n\n    Fix issue #920.\n\ndiff --git a/libyara/parser.c b/libyara/parser.c\nindex 6789a341..dd696f6d 100644\n--- a/libyara/parser.c\n+++ b/libyara/parser.c\n@@ -730,7 +730,7 @@ int yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1(\n       yr_hash_table_lookup(\n         compiler->objects_table,\n         identifier,\n-        compiler->current_namespace->name) != NULL)\n+        NULL) != NULL)\n   {\n     // A rule or variable with the same identifier already exists, return the\n     // appropriate error.\ndiff --git a/tests/test-api.c b/tests/test-api.c\nindex b2c5ef8d..c0877e7c 100644\n--- a/tests/test-api.c\n+++ b/tests/test-api.c\n@@ -694,6 +694,42 @@ void test_rules_stats()\n }\n \n \n+void test_issue_920()\n+{\n+  const char* rules_str = \"\\\n+      rule test { \\\n+        condition: true \\\n+      }\";\n+\n+  YR_COMPILER* compiler = NULL;\n+\n+  yr_initialize();\n+\n+  if (yr_compiler_create(&compiler) != ERROR_SUCCESS)\n+  {\n+    perror(\"yr_compiler_create\");\n+    exit(EXIT_FAILURE);\n+  }\n+\n+  // Define a variable named \"test\"\n+  yr_compiler_define_boolean_variable(compiler, \"test\", 1);\n+\n+  // The compilation should not succeed, as the rule is named \"test\" and a\n+  // a variable with the same name already exists.\n+  yr_compiler_add_string(compiler, rules_str, NULL);\n+\n+  if (compiler->last_error != ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER)\n+  {\n+    yr_compiler_destroy(compiler);\n+    printf(\"expecting ERROR_CALLBACK_REQUIRED (%d), got: %d\\n\",\n+           ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER, compiler->last_error);\n+    exit(EXIT_FAILURE);\n+  }\n+\n+  yr_compiler_destroy(compiler);\n+  yr_finalize();\n+}\n+\n int main(int argc, char** argv)\n {\n   test_disabled_rules();\n@@ -704,6 +740,8 @@ int main(int argc, char** argv)\n   test_save_load_rules();\n   test_scanner();\n   test_ast_callback();\n-  test_issue_834();\n   test_rules_stats();\n+\n+  test_issue_834();\n+  test_issue_920();\n }","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_012JwPVZ5wMXFdVWiDUbSwo3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! Now I understand the bug completely. The fix for issue #920 changed the second yr_hash_table_lookup call's namespace parameter from `compiler->current_namespace->name` to `NULL`. This is the correct fix.\n\nThe buggy version has it reversed:\n- The original code had `compiler->current_namespace->name` (buggy)\n- The fix changed it to `NULL` (correct)\n- The current buggy code has been reverted back to use `compiler->current_namespace->name` (which is the buggy state again)\n\nWait, let me re-read the diff. The commit \"buggy\" (fb1e636b) changed:\n- FROM: `NULL)` \n- TO: `compiler->current_namespace->name) != NULL)`\n\nBut the fix commit (cb787cc0) changed:\n- FROM: `compiler->current_namespace->name) != NULL)`\n- TO: `NULL) != NULL)`\n\nSo the buggy commit is undoing the fix!\n\nNow let me understand WHY using NULL is correct. Looking at the logic:\n\n```c\nif (yr_hash_table_lookup(compiler->rules_table, identifier, compiler->current_namespace->name) != NULL ||\n    yr_hash_table_lookup(compiler->objects_table, identifier, NULL) != NULL)\n```\n\nWhen looking in rules_table, we're looking for a rule in the current namespace. But when looking in objects_table (which contains variables), we should be looking across ALL namespaces (namespace=NULL). This makes sense because issue #920 was about detecting when a variable named \"test\" already exists when trying to create a rule named \"test\".\n\nSo the bug is that the code is looking for the variable in the current namespace only, when it should be looking across all namespaces. This means it's not detecting the duplicate identifier properly.\n\nLet me verify this by understanding what happens in the test:\n1. A boolean variable \"test\" is defined (this goes into objects_table)\n\n\n2. Then we try to define a rule \"test\" \n3. The code should detect the duplicate and set compiler->last_error to ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER\n4. But because it's looking in the wrong namespace for the variable, it doesn't find it\n5. So compiler->last_error remains 0 (not set)\n\nThis explains why the test fails - the duplicate identifier check isn't working because the namespace parameter is restricting the search when it shouldn't be.\n\nThe real issue is in how the code searches for existing identifiers. It's passing the current namespace when it should pass NULL to search across all namespaces. Variables defined globally or in other scopes won't be found with the current approach, so the duplicate detection fails silently.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1235,"cache_read_input_tokens":59242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1235},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3add790f-caa9-4081-a140-ecdff77df695","uuid":"cdf0d79d-57af-42d8-a2d5-0f0ad11ecaf1"}
